<a href="https://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/jump?iu=0&sz=1&c=234" target="_blank"><img src="https://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/ad?iu=0&sz=1&c=234" border="0" alt=""></a>The money truck and a backup truck were ambushed by the thugs on Tuesday morning in Modderfontein, Joburg. They were armed with 9mm pistols and R5 rifles.The robbers surprised the backup truck, manned by two officers aged 34 and 29.They opened fire and one of the officers died at the scene. The other one died in hospital. The thugs tried to blow up the money truck but they couldn’t access the money. They left the scene empty-handed!Fidelity CEO Wahl Bartmann has sent his heartfelt condolences to the families of the two officers. “We are really sad to lose such excellent officers. The killing was senseless and cannot be condoned,” he said.Police spokesman Captain Kay Makhubele said police are investigating two counts each of murder and robbery.Makhubele said the thugs were driving a Golf 7, Audi and Hyundai H1.No arrests have been made.